Config and style css files for hyprland and waybar, just install Sway and Waybar and place them in ~/.config/hyprland ~/.config/swayidle and ~/.config/waybar respectively. 
You can of course tweak the startup programs, bg image and resolutions to your liking depending on your setup in hyprland.conf

## Essential Packages:
ttf-roboto
ttf-ubuntu-font-family
ttf-font-awesome
otf-font-awesome
noto-fonts-emoji
tbsm
hyprland
hyprpaper
swayidle
waybar
alacritty
grim (screenshot functionality)
slurp (screen selection utility for grim)
mako (notification system)
gnome-polkit (pkexec needed by some guis for root access)
gsettings-desktop-schemas (needed for setting cursor theme)

## Xwayland Packages:
xorg-server-xwayland
xhost (needed for xwayland root access)

